<div class="post-15207 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-fi-news tag-website">
<a href="https://www.flaginstitute.org/wp/fi-news/website-update/"  title="Website update"><img src="https://www.flaginstitute.org/wp/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/UK-County-Flags-2023-100x100.png" alt=""  width="100"  height="100"  class="woo-image thumbnail alignleft" /></a><h2 class="title"><a href="https://www.flaginstitute.org/wp/fi-news/website-update/" rel="bookmark" title="Website update">Website update</a></h2><div class="post-meta"><span class="small">By</span> <span class="author vcard"><span class="fn"><a href="https://www.flaginstitute.org/wp/author/admin_james/" title="Posts by Webmaster" rel="author">Webmaster</a></span></span> <span class="small">on</span> <abbr class="date time published" title="2024-02-12T15:38:30+0000">12 February 2024</abbr>  <span class="small">in</span> <span class="categories"><a href="https://www.flaginstitute.org/wp/category/fi-news/">FI News</a></span>   </div>
	<div class="entry">
	    <p>While we update our website, online joining and renewal options may be temporarily unavailable. But please don&#8217;t despair. You can still join the Flag Institute or renew your membership. Simply click on this post to email the Flag Institute Administrator, or call 07935 973072 (answerphone), and we&#8217;ll be in touch. &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>
	</div><!-- /.entry -->
