<div class="post-15180 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-fi-news tag-conferences">
<a href="https://www.flaginstitute.org/wp/fi-news/flag-institute-spring-conference-2024-book-now/"  title="Flag Institute Spring Conference 2024 &#8211; book now"><img src="https://www.flaginstitute.org/wp/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Conway-Hall-Library-Room-100x100.jpg" alt="Conway Hall Library Room showing bookcases, tables and chairs"  width="100"  height="100"  class="woo-image thumbnail alignleft" /></a><h2 class="title"><a href="https://www.flaginstitute.org/wp/fi-news/flag-institute-spring-conference-2024-book-now/" rel="bookmark" title="Flag Institute Spring Conference 2024 &#8211; book now">Flag Institute Spring Conference 2024 &#8211; book now</a></h2><div class="post-meta"><span class="small">By</span> <span class="author vcard"><span class="fn"><a href="https://www.flaginstitute.org/wp/author/admin_james/" title="Posts by Webmaster" rel="author">Webmaster</a></span></span> <span class="small">on</span> <abbr class="date time published" title="2024-01-29T11:57:08+0000">29 January 2024</abbr>  <span class="small">in</span> <span class="categories"><a href="https://www.flaginstitute.org/wp/category/fi-news/">FI News</a></span>   </div>
	<div class="entry">
	    <p>Booking is now open for the Flag Institute Spring Conference 2024, taking place in central London on Saturday 18 May, 9.30am–5pm. As ever we&#8217;ll be showcasing a mix of contemporary and historical vexillological presentations. Speakers will include Brian Cham on the Tino Rangatiratanga Flag (Maori Flag). Further announcements will follow shortly. The registration fee is [&hellip;]</p>
	</div><!-- /.entry -->
