<div class="post-14368 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-fi-news">
<a title="Commander Bruce Nicolls RN" href="https://www.flaginstitute.org/wp/fi-news/commander-bruce-nicolls-rn/" ><img src="https://www.flaginstitute.org/wp/wp-content/themes/canvas/functions/thumb.php?src=wp/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/nicolls-bruce.jpg&#038;w=100&#038;h=100&#038;zc=1&#038;q=90" alt="" class="woo-image thumbnail alignleft"  width="100"  height="100"  /></a><h2 class="title"><a href="https://www.flaginstitute.org/wp/fi-news/commander-bruce-nicolls-rn/" rel="bookmark" title="Commander Bruce Nicolls RN">Commander Bruce Nicolls RN</a></h2><div class="post-meta"><span class="small">By</span> <span class="author vcard"><span class="fn"><a href="https://www.flaginstitute.org/wp/author/admin_james/" title="Posts by Webmaster" rel="author">Webmaster</a></span></span> <span class="small">on</span> <abbr class="date time published" title="2023-07-12T16:30:55+0100">12 July 2023</abbr>  <span class="small">in</span> <span class="categories"><a href="https://www.flaginstitute.org/wp/category/fi-news/">FI News</a></span>   </div>
	<div class="entry">
	    <p>We are sad to report that Commander Bruce Nicolls RN died on 2 July 2023 at the age of 91. Bruce served in the Royal Navy (1946–82), where he first became interested in vexillology and heraldry. He was a prolific designer of flags, including those of Guernsey, the Mary Rose Trust and the Royal Naval [&hellip;]</p>
	</div><!-- /.entry -->
	<div class="fix"></div>
	<div class="post-more">   
