<div class="post-14353 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-fi-news category-uk-flag-registry-news tag-berwickshire tag-community-flags tag-county-flags tag-scotland">
<a href="https://www.flaginstitute.org/wp/uk-flag-registry-news/flag-for-berwickshire/"  title="Flag for Berwickshire"><img src="https://www.flaginstitute.org/wp/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Berwickshire-Greenknowe-Tower-100x100.jpeg" alt="Greenknowe Tower, Berwickshire"  width="100"  height="100"  class="woo-image thumbnail alignleft" /></a><h2 class="title"><a href="https://www.flaginstitute.org/wp/uk-flag-registry-news/flag-for-berwickshire/" rel="bookmark" title="Flag for Berwickshire">Flag for Berwickshire</a></h2><div class="post-meta"><span class="small">By</span> <span class="author vcard"><span class="fn"><a href="https://www.flaginstitute.org/wp/author/admin_james/" title="Posts by Webmaster" rel="author">Webmaster</a></span></span> <span class="small">on</span> <abbr class="date time published" title="2023-07-11T14:02:36+0100">11 July 2023</abbr>  <span class="small">in</span> <span class="categories"><a href="https://www.flaginstitute.org/wp/category/fi-news/">FI News</a>, <a href="https://www.flaginstitute.org/wp/category/uk-flag-registry-news/">UK Flag Registry News</a></span>   </div>
	<div class="entry">
	    <p>Design an official flag for Berwickshire! That&#8217;s the challenge to groups and individuals set by a new competition launched last month. The contest – run by Berwickshire Civic Society with support from the Fallago Environment Fund – offers a first prize of £250. The Court of Lord Lyon and the Flag Institute will also register [&hellip;]</p>
	</div><!-- /.entry -->
