<div class="post-14280 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-fi-news tag-union-flag tag-union-jack tag-united-kingdom">
<a href="https://www.flaginstitute.org/wp/fi-news/knit-your-own-union-jack/"  title="Knit your own Union Jack?"><img src="https://www.flaginstitute.org/wp/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Katie-Ayers-Union-Jack_004-scaled-e1683207382863-100x100.jpg" alt="Katie Ayers displays her knitted Union Jack"  width="100"  height="100"  class="woo-image thumbnail alignleft" /></a><h2 class="title"><a href="https://www.flaginstitute.org/wp/fi-news/knit-your-own-union-jack/" rel="bookmark" title="Knit your own Union Jack?">Knit your own Union Jack?</a></h2><div class="post-meta"><span class="small">By</span> <span class="author vcard"><span class="fn"><a href="https://www.flaginstitute.org/wp/author/admin_james/" title="Posts by Webmaster" rel="author">Webmaster</a></span></span> <span class="small">on</span> <abbr class="date time published" title="2023-05-04T14:40:43+0100">4 May 2023</abbr>  <span class="small">in</span> <span class="categories"><a href="https://www.flaginstitute.org/wp/category/fi-news/">FI News</a></span>   </div>
	<div class="entry">
	    <p>Knit your own Union Jack? Why not? Buckinghamshire-based Katie Ayers set herself this challenge and turned to us for vital information. Our Union Flag Specification gave her the correct proportions to plot the number of stitches. Then she started with a number of smaller examples&#8230; and just kept going. You can see a proud Katie [&hellip;]</p>
	</div><!-- /.entry -->
	<div class="fix"></div>
